TY  - JOUR
AU  - Matta, Rafael
AU  - Perotti, Enrico
T1  - Pay, Stay, or Delay? How to Settle a Run
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhad084
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 37
IS  - 4
SP  - 1368
EP  - 1407
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - The classic view assumes banks prioritize immediate repayment by selling assets until default. We endogenize run frequency and study how general settlement rules trade off liquidity provision net of fire sale losses against induced run incentives. Panic runs are eliminated when all illiquid assets are sold under orderly resolution, but liquidity provision in a run is minimal. When suspension after some fire sales is followed by immediate liquidation, run frequency falls then rises in suspension delay. Thus, optimal suspension may require some sale of illiquid assets, in contrast to MMF norms. Ex post discretion induces excessive liquidation and more frequent runs. (JEL D8, G21)
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhad084
ER  - 



